   "source": [
    "# Importing EPRpy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import eprpy as epr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "# Data (1D)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

    "tempo = epr.load('tempo.DSC')"

   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

   "source": [
    "type(tempo) # tempo is an EprData object"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Plotting"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

  },
  {

   "metadata": {},

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Formatting plots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Use attributes directly to plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* Alternatively, plots can be made directly using matplotlib and ``EprData`` attributes with full control over formatting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 371,
       "width": 640
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "fig,ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,4))\n",
    "ax.plot(tempo.x/10,tempo.data,color='black') # convert Gauss to mT\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Magnetic Field [mT]') # set x axis label\n",
    "_=ax.set_yticks([]) # hide intensity\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Operations on Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Scaling data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "After scaling : \n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 290,
       "width": 390
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# import EPRpy\n",
    "import eprpy as epr\n",
    "\n",
    "# load data\n",
    "tempo = epr.load('tempo.DSC')\n",
    "\n",
    "# scale between -1 and 1\n",
    "tempo.scale_between(-1,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('After scaling : ')\n",
    "fig,ax = tempo.plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Baseline correction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 290,
       "width": 390
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# import EPRpy\n",
    "import eprpy as epr\n",
    "\n",
    "# load data\n",
    "tempo = epr.load('tempo.DSC')\n",
    "\n",
    "# linear baseline correction\n",
    "tempo.baseline_correct() # default is linear baseline correction using 10 points at the start and end of the data.\n",
    "fig,ax = tempo.plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Computing integrals"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 290,
       "width": 390
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# import EPRpy\n",
    "import eprpy as epr\n",
    "\n",
    "# load data\n",
    "tempo = epr.load('tempo.DSC')\n",
    "\n",
    "# baseline correction and integration\n",
    "tempo.baseline_correct()\n",
    "tempo.integral()\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot the absorption signal\n",
    "fig,ax = tempo.plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Selecting a region"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* For this example, we assume that the desired region is  the low field hyperfine line."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Full spectrum : \n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 413,
       "width": 568
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# import EPRpy\n",
    "import eprpy as epr\n",
    "\n",
    "# load data\n",
    "tempo = epr.load('tempo.DSC')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the data using an array with unity spacing to find corresponding indices\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "print('Full spectrum : ')\n",
    "_=plt.plot(tempo.data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# make a new EprData object corresponding to the desired region\n",
    "tempo_region = tempo.select_region(range(550,850)) # indices from 0 to 900"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Selected region : \n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 290,
       "width": 390
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# selected region, note that the the new EprData object tempo_region only has the data corresponding to this region\n",
    "print('Selected region : ')\n",
    "fig,ax = tempo_region.plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## History of data operations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "EPRpy allows for keeping a log of data operations done on an EprData object, as long as in-built functions are used."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# import EPRpy\n",
    "import eprpy as epr\n",
    "\n",
    "# load data\n",
    "tempo = epr.load('tempo.DSC')\n",
    "\n",
    "# do some operations\n",
    "tempo.scale_between(-1,1)\n",
    "tempo.baseline_correct()\n",
    "tempo.integral()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Access history"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* Each ``EprData`` object stores history of all data operations and the corresponding ``EprData`` object in a list of lists. The first item in each list is the description of the data operation and the second item is the corresponding ``EprData`` object."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[['2025-01-14 11:15:48.500996 : Data loaded from tempo.DSC.',\n",
       "  <eprpy.loader.EprData at 0x1165e10a0>],\n",
       " ['2025-01-14 11:15:48.503469 : Data scaled between -1 and 1.',\n",
       "  <eprpy.loader.EprData at 0x117a8cce0>],\n",
       " ['2025-01-14 11:15:48.504666 : Baseline corrected',\n",
       "  <eprpy.loader.EprData at 0x1164b1af0>],\n",
       " ['2025-01-14 11:15:48.506104 : Integral calculated',\n",
       "  <eprpy.loader.EprData at 0x117a2c890>]]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 31,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "tempo.history"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "* To plot or access a specific ``EprData`` from the history, simply use indexing. For instance, to view the original data again, plot the first item in history:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "2025-01-14 11:15:48.500996 : Data loaded from tempo.DSC.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {

       "width": 390
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(tempo.history[0][0])\n",
    "fig,ax = tempo.history[0][1].plot() "
